title: Robust Pixel-Level Crack Detection Using Deep Fully Convolutional Neural Networks
venue: Journal of computing in civil engineering
tldr:
TLDR
This paper introduces the idea of using deep fully convolutional neural networks for pixel-level defect detection in concrete infrastructure systems and shows how coarse patch-level deep learning can be abused in this situation.

title: Federated Semisupervised Learning for Attack Detection in Industrial Internet of Things
tldr:
TLDR
A novel federated semisupervised learning scheme that takes advantage of both unlabeled and labeled data in a federated way and ensures that no local private data is exchanged and works even when only a few amounts of labeled data are available.

title: D ec 2 01 6 Improved Dropout for Shallow and Deep Learning
tldr:
TLDR
An efficient adaptive dropout (namedolutional dropout) is proposed that computes the sampling probabilities on-the-fly from a mini-batch of examples that achieves not only much faster convergence and but also a smaller testing error than the standard dropout.
